Editor Manual 3
Join
SIGNUP button click and fill in the blank.
Privacy Policy is a required.
Email, Nickname must be duplicated check.
Email, Name, Nickname, Password are required.
If you click SIGNUP button, a verification email will be sent to the email you
entered.
If you click email verification link in verification email, it will be verification
completed.
Editor Manual 4
Email verification is a must. You can't use the service without Email
verification.
Find password
First, Please enter your email.
After then, click Forget password . Your new password will be sent to you by
email.
Top bar
There are major functions of 'DABOOK'
You can edit the ebook by moving the tabs.
Editor Manual 5
FILE
Create ebook
You can create a new ebook.
It will be create to click CREATE E-BOOK button.
You can enter the ebook name, location to save the ebook and cover image.
If no image is entered, the default image will be used.
Editor Manual 6
Load ebook
You can import an existing ebook folder and continue editing it.
It can import to use LOAD button.
If it is not an ebook folder, it cannot be loaded.
If the ebook folder cannot be loaded, check the folder. There should be EPUB,
METAINF and mimetype as below.
If an error message appears at the bottom right after loading, check the
folders and files at the bottom. The folders and files below are required.
Editor Manual 7
Load from server
You can bring up the ebook list of user id.
Loading Process
Click the LOAD FROM SERVER button to see a list of all ebooks
Editor Manual 8
Select the ebook you want and click Download button.
The selected ebook will be download in zip file format.
When the download is complete, Load from server Dialog turns off and a
message appears in the lower right corner.
Unzip the download zip file.
Load the Unzip file using LOAD button
SAVE
You can save changes to the file.
It is also stored on the server.
Shortcut : ctrl+s
Before Create Epub button click, It is essential to save.
Editor Manual 9
Chapter
You can add chapters from the ebook.
Chapter's name is required and can be duplicated.
When creating a chapter in the ebook folder, it can occur error. Please use
Chapter button.
Create epub
You can save the created ebook as an epub file.
Click the Create epub button and write the name of the ebook and author.
Click export button to save the epub file.
Editor Manual 10
Edit
Undo
Shortcut : ctrl+q
If you use ctrl+z [system shortcut] , undo and redo functions may not
work.
Redo
Shortcut : ctrl+f
If you use ctrl+y [system shortcut] , undo and redo functions may not work.
Cut
Shortcut : ctrl+w
Copy
Editor Manual 11
Shortcut : ctrl+e
Copy
Shortcut : ctrl+d
Find
Input the searching word.
You can cheak the number of identical words.
You can check objects to find through the Up and Down Icon.
Replace word
You can replace word with word you want.
All : Change all words at once.
Aa : replace case-insensitively.
Editor Manual 12
Tool
Some functions required dragging. When click the button without dragging,
the tag is not added.
Title
Dragging required
You can use H1 ~ H6 title tag.
Italic
Dragging required
Enter
P tag is created so that it can be recognized as a paragraph by pressing the
enter key in the input window.
You want to change line in same paragraph, you must use enter button.

Link
Editor Manual 14
Dragging required
You can connect the link to the sentence you want.
After dragging the text you want, click the link button and write the url.
Please write a correct url. Entering the wrong url may not work.
Table
You can create a table of any size.
Table have table name and table.
Style
Align
You can align by paragraph.
Place the cursor on the paragraph to be aligned and press the button.
Font color
Setting font color
You can specify the color you want.
Right-Clicking the A button pop up the color selection window.
Editor Manual 15
Using font color
Dragging required
You can change the color you want.
Dragging the text to change the text color.
Left-Clicking the A button to change the text color.
Background color
Setting background color
You can specify the color you want.
Right-Clicking the button pop up the color selection window.
Editor Manual 16
Using background color
Dragging required
You can change the color you want.
Dragging the text to change the text color.
Left-Clicking the button to change the text color.
Font
You can change the font in any paragraph you want.
A total of 9 fonts are supported.
Place the cursor on the paragraph to be apply and press the Font button.
Choose the font you want and press the APPLY button.
Editor Manual 17
Font size
Dragging required
You can change the font size to use expand font size , reduce font size button.
Dragging the text to change the font size.
And then, the expand font size , reduce font size button press.
My style
You can use customizing style through My style .
You can apply the My style by paragraph.
Using My style
Dragging required
Editor Manual 18
Dragging the paragraph to apply.
Click the My style button and choose the style name you want.
Making My style
You can add My style to click add style button.
Align, Font, Background color and Font color can be customized.
Align, Font, Background color and Font color is not required.
Style names cannot be duplicated.
Editor Manual 19
Only number, korean and special symbols _ can be used for the style name.
Otherwise, an error may occur.

Editor Manual 24
Delete Chapter
You can delete the chapter.
Click the trash can button and the selected chapter is deleted.
The delete chapter cannot be recovered.
When deleting a chapter in the ebook folder, it can occur error. Please use
trash can button.
